00:47:44.296 --> 00:47:46.630
 

00:47:46.630 --> 00:47:49.670
AUDIENCE: Hi Dikembe,
how's it going?

00:47:49.670 --> 00:47:50.430
My name is Mattie.

00:47:50.430 --> 00:47:51.760
I'm from Finland.

00:47:51.760 --> 00:47:54.305
And I just wanted to
ask you a question,

00:47:54.305 --> 00:47:55.930
because something
that we see in Europe

00:47:55.930 --> 00:47:58.940
is that with the country's
not doing so well,

00:47:58.940 --> 00:48:01.290
there's a big rise
in countries--

00:48:01.290 --> 00:48:03.240
there's political
pressures of countries

00:48:03.240 --> 00:48:07.190
not to do as much foreign
aid or take in refugees.

00:48:07.190 --> 00:48:10.320
And I wanted to see what
your opinion on something

00:48:10.320 --> 00:48:12.440
that you're doing as a
non-government organization

00:48:12.440 --> 00:48:15.420
versus governmental foreign
aid, and how you see,

00:48:15.420 --> 00:48:19.310
for example, what's happening
in Europe, at the moment.

00:48:19.310 --> 00:48:24.110
DIKEMBE MUTOMBO: I've been a
big advocate about the issue

00:48:24.110 --> 00:48:27.805
that we are dealing with
today about foreign aid.

00:48:27.805 --> 00:48:32.730
I think it should not be just
the European country, something

00:48:32.730 --> 00:48:36.680
[INAUDIBLE], has been
a student of diplomacy.

00:48:36.680 --> 00:48:39.450
I think they have given so
much aid in the [INAUDIBLE],

00:48:39.450 --> 00:48:41.760
they will go and get it back.

00:48:41.760 --> 00:48:43.720
It was like a death.

00:48:43.720 --> 00:48:46.790
They're letting an African
country borrow money.

00:48:46.790 --> 00:48:49.250
And I think when they
were borrowing money,

00:48:49.250 --> 00:48:52.490
that money never reached
the African people.

00:48:52.490 --> 00:48:54.720
It was staying just
in all those leaders

00:48:54.720 --> 00:48:58.610
who went to Europe to
negotiate from a Paris club,

00:48:58.610 --> 00:49:00.510
European club, and all of that.

00:49:00.510 --> 00:49:03.890
That money was staying just in
Europe in the bank accounts.

00:49:03.890 --> 00:49:06.390
And I didn't think
we're in the right place

00:49:06.390 --> 00:49:10.814
really to name all those leaders
who took billions of dollars

00:49:10.814 --> 00:49:11.480
from the people.

00:49:11.480 --> 00:49:15.740
But if any countries
around the world

00:49:15.740 --> 00:49:18.810
can go to the continent of
Africa or South America,

00:49:18.810 --> 00:49:23.200
and invest in a society
and make a difference

00:49:23.200 --> 00:49:27.250
in those communities,
and leave few people

00:49:27.250 --> 00:49:30.310
from the organizations there to
just watch what they're doing,

00:49:30.310 --> 00:49:35.110
and they hire the community to
be responsible, or work there,

00:49:35.110 --> 00:49:40.990
that's what we did, even though
I do run the Biamba Marie

00:49:40.990 --> 00:49:42.570
Mutombo Hospital from the US.

00:49:42.570 --> 00:49:47.830
But we have more than 12 people
on the ground, Congolese,

00:49:47.830 --> 00:49:50.400
that we hire, we train.

00:49:50.400 --> 00:49:55.980
We made them be responsible
for this $40 million facility,

00:49:55.980 --> 00:49:58.130
and to make sure to
keep an eye on it.

00:49:58.130 --> 00:50:00.590
They watch each other.

00:50:00.590 --> 00:50:01.900
That's what you have to do.

00:50:01.900 --> 00:50:06.020
And you have to make sure that
the society's responsible.

00:50:06.020 --> 00:50:10.215
Do not just come and then open
the library, build the library,

00:50:10.215 --> 00:50:12.350
and enable [INAUDIBLE].

00:50:12.350 --> 00:50:12.880
Say, OK.

00:50:12.880 --> 00:50:14.330
I already gave you a gift.

00:50:14.330 --> 00:50:17.610
I'm not responsible if the
library closes down, or what.

00:50:17.610 --> 00:50:20.900
That's the big failure
that we have seen.

00:50:20.900 --> 00:50:23.040
And that's why people
